From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lusoris <lusoris@pm.me>
Date: Mon, 27 Apr 2026 09:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] libvmaf: add libvmaf_vulkan filter (zero-copy VkImage import)

Introduces a dedicated `libvmaf_vulkan` FFmpeg filter that consumes
Vulkan-decoded frames (`AVFrame->data[0] -> AVVkFrame*`), pulls the
Y-plane VkImage + layout + timeline semaphore from the AVVkFrame, and
routes it through `vmaf_vulkan_import_image` /
`vmaf_vulkan_read_imported_pictures` for a zero-copy import path
without the `hwdownload,format=yuv420p` round-trip the regular
`libvmaf` filter forces.

Pairs with the C-API surfaces in
libvmaf/include/libvmaf/libvmaf_vulkan.h:
  - vmaf_vulkan_state_init_external (adopts FFmpeg's VkInstance/
    VkDevice so source VkImage handles are valid on libvmaf's
    compute device — same-device requirement)
  - vmaf_vulkan_import_state
  - vmaf_vulkan_import_image (Y plane only)
  - vmaf_vulkan_wait_compute (per-frame synchronisation barrier)
  - vmaf_vulkan_read_imported_pictures (route to scoring pipeline)

Closes T7-29 part 3 in the fork backlog. Companion to the existing
0004-libvmaf-wire-vulkan-backend-selector.patch (which adds the
vulkan_device option to the regular libvmaf filter); together the
two patches give users:

  * libvmaf=vulkan_device=N    — software frames + Vulkan compute
  * libvmaf_vulkan=...         — Vulkan hwdec + zero-copy import

v1 import path is synchronous (fence-wait inside import_image);
v2 async pending-fence model is a deferred follow-up. See
docs/adr/0186-vulkan-image-import-impl.md.

Patch is on top of 0001-0005 (post-libvmaf_sycl-filter baseline).

---
diff --git a/configure b/configure
index 41738050f0..3b3f0f1d13 100755
